<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="130" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1636,2023]" pageId="27" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1815,1840]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="130" reason="1">Discussion.</emphasis>
The taxon requires further scrutiny. It seems quite possible, that several species are mixed up under the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malaise &amp; Benson" authorityYear="1934" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[330,468,1852,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Arge" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rustica">
<emphasis box="[330,468,1852,1876]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="130">Arge rustica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Currently about 10 nominal taxa are treated as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malaise &amp; Benson" authorityYear="1934" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1156,1265,1852,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Arge" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rustica">
<emphasis box="[1156,1265,1852,1876]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="130">A. rustica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Recent results of COI barcoding show four different clusters for specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malaise &amp; Benson" authorityYear="1934" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[992,1103,1888,1911]" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Arge" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rustica">
<emphasis box="[992,1103,1888,1911]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="130">A. rustica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Referring to 
<bibRefCitation author="Konow, F. W." box="[1264,1431,1887,1912]" pageId="27" pageNumber="130" pagination="203 - 207" refId="ref17770" refString="Konow, F. W. (1899) Chalastogastrorum novae species et varietates, quas D. Escalera ex Asia minore reportavit. Actas de la Sociedad Espanola de Historia Natural, 28 (7), 203 - 207." type="journal article" year="1899">Konow (1899)</bibRefCitation>
, the taxon was after its description only mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schedl, W." box="[765,917,1924,1949]" pageId="27" pageNumber="130" pagination="1609 - 1630" refId="ref19231" refString="Schedl, W. (2009) Die Pflanzenwespen von Syrien (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) - ein Uberblick. Linzer biologische Beitrage, 41 (2), 1609 - 1630." type="journal article" year="2009">Schedl (2009</bibRefCitation>
, for 
<collectingCountry box="[971,1032,1924,1949]" name="Syria" pageId="27" pageNumber="130">Syria</collectingCountry>
) and in synonymy lists of catalogs. However, even if the locality Akbés in the late 19 
<superScript attach="left" box="[718,730,1959,1973]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="130">th</superScript>
and early 20 
<superScript attach="left" box="[879,891,1959,1973]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="130">th</superScript>
century has been associated with “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1290,1353,1962,1987]" name="Syria" pageId="27" pageNumber="130">Syria</collectingCountry>
” in the historical sense, it belongs today to 
<collectingCountry box="[551,633,1998,2023]" name="Turkey" pageId="27" pageNumber="130">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
